crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The PHP script presents a web form with a text input field labeled "cmd" and a submit button labeled "Execute". When the form is submitted via the GET method, the script checks if the 'cmd' parameter is present in the URL. If it is, the script executes the value of the 'cmd' parameter as a system command using the `system()` function. The output of the command, including standard error, is displayed within `<pre>` tags on the webpage.
